{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"My story is a little bit about war."},{"time":4000,"text":"It's about disillusionment."},{"time":6000,"text":"It's about death."},{"time":8000,"text":"And it's about rediscovering"},{"time":10000,"text":"idealism"},{"time":12000,"text":"in all of that wreckage."},{"time":14000,"text":"And perhaps also, there's a lesson"},{"time":16000,"text":"about how to deal with"},{"time":18000,"text":"our screwed-up, fragmenting"},{"time":21000,"text":"and dangerous world of the 21st century."},{"time":25000,"text":"I don't believe in straightforward narratives."},{"time":28000,"text":"I don't believe in a life or history"},{"time":30000,"text":"written as decision \"A\" led to consequence \"B\""},{"time":33000,"text":"led to consequence \"C\" --"},{"time":35000,"text":"these neat narratives that we're presented with,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and that perhaps we encourage in each other."},{"time":40000,"text":"I believe in randomness,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and one of the reasons I believe that"},{"time":44000,"text":"is because me becoming a diplomat was random."},{"time":47000,"text":"I'm colorblind."},{"time":49000,"text":"I was born unable to see most colors."},{"time":51000,"text":"This is why I wear gray and black most of the time,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and I have to take my wife with me"},{"time":56000,"text":"to chose clothes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"And I'd always wanted to be a fighter pilot when I was a boy."},{"time":62000,"text":"I loved watching planes barrel over"},{"time":64000,"text":"our holiday home in the countryside."},{"time":67000,"text":"And it was my boyhood dream to be a fighter pilot."},{"time":70000,"text":"And I did the tests in the Royal Air Force to become a pilot,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and sure enough, I failed."},{"time":75000,"text":"I couldn't see all the blinking different lights,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and I can't distinguish color."},{"time":79000,"text":"So I had to choose another career,"},{"time":81000,"text":"and this was in fact relatively easy for me,"},{"time":84000,"text":"because I had an abiding passion all the way through my childhood,"},{"time":87000,"text":"which was international relations."},{"time":89000,"text":"As a child,"},{"time":91000,"text":"I read the newspaper thoroughly."},{"time":94000,"text":"I was fascinated by the Cold War,"},{"time":96000,"text":"by the INF negotiations"},{"time":98000,"text":"over intermediate-range nuclear missiles,"},{"time":101000,"text":"the proxy war between the Soviet Union and the U.S."},{"time":104000,"text":"in Angola or Afghanistan."},{"time":107000,"text":"These things really interested me."},{"time":110000,"text":"And so I decided quite at an early age"},{"time":112000,"text":"I wanted to be a diplomat."},{"time":114000,"text":"And I, one day, I announced this to my parents --"},{"time":117000,"text":"and my father denies this story to this day --"},{"time":119000,"text":"I said, \"Daddy, I want to be a diplomat.\""},{"time":121000,"text":"And he turned to me, and he said,"},{"time":123000,"text":"\"Carne, you have to be very clever to be a diplomat.\""},{"time":125000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":127000,"text":"And my ambition was sealed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"In 1989,"},{"time":132000,"text":"I entered the British Foreign Service."},{"time":135000,"text":"That year, 5,000 people applied to become a diplomat,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and 20 of us succeeded."},{"time":140000,"text":"And as those numbers suggest,"},{"time":143000,"text":"I was inducted into an elite"},{"time":146000,"text":"and fascinating and exhilarating world."},{"time":150000,"text":"Being a diplomat, then and now,"},{"time":152000,"text":"is an incredible job, and I loved every minute of it --"},{"time":155000,"text":"I enjoyed the status of it."},{"time":157000,"text":"I bought myself a nice suit and wore leather-soled shoes"},{"time":160000,"text":"and reveled in"},{"time":162000,"text":"this amazing access I had to world events."},{"time":165000,"text":"I traveled to the Gaza Strip."},{"time":167000,"text":"I headed the Middle East Peace Process section"},{"time":169000,"text":"in the British Foreign Ministry."},{"time":171000,"text":"I became a speechwriter"},{"time":173000,"text":"for the British Foreign Secretary."},{"time":175000,"text":"I met Yasser Arafat."},{"time":177000,"text":"I negotiated"},{"time":179000,"text":"with Saddam's diplomats at the U.N."},{"time":182000,"text":"Later, I traveled to Kabul"},{"time":184000,"text":"and served in Afghanistan after the fall of the Taliban."},{"time":187000,"text":"And I would travel"},{"time":189000,"text":"in a C-130 transport"},{"time":192000,"text":"and go and visit warlords"},{"time":194000,"text":"in mountain hideaways"},{"time":196000,"text":"and negotiate with them"},{"time":198000,"text":"about how we were going to eradicate Al Qaeda from Afghanistan,"},{"time":201000,"text":"surrounded by my Special Forces escort,"},{"time":204000,"text":"who, themselves, had to have an escort of a platoon of Royal Marines,"},{"time":207000,"text":"because it was so dangerous."},{"time":209000,"text":"And that was exciting -- that was fun."},{"time":212000,"text":"It was really interesting."},{"time":214000,"text":"And it's a great cadre of people,"},{"time":216000,"text":"incredibly close-knit community of people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"And the pinnacle of my career, as it turned out,"},{"time":222000,"text":"was when I was posted to New York."},{"time":225000,"text":"I'd already served in Germany, Norway,"},{"time":227000,"text":"various other places,"},{"time":229000,"text":"but I was posted to New York"},{"time":231000,"text":"to serve on the U.N. Security Council for the British delegation."},{"time":234000,"text":"And my responsibility was the Middle East,"},{"time":236000,"text":"which was my specialty."},{"time":238000,"text":"And there, I dealt with things"},{"time":240000,"text":"like the Middle East peace process,"},{"time":242000,"text":"the Lockerbie issue --"},{"time":244000,"text":"we can talk about that later, if you wish --"},{"time":247000,"text":"but above all, my responsibility was Iraq"},{"time":249000,"text":"and its weapons of mass destruction"},{"time":251000,"text":"and the sanctions we placed on Iraq"},{"time":253000,"text":"to oblige it to disarm itself of these weapons."},{"time":257000,"text":"I was the chief British negotiator"},{"time":259000,"text":"on the subject,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and I was steeped in the issue."},{"time":264000,"text":"And anyway,"},{"time":267000,"text":"my tour -- it was kind of a very exciting time."},{"time":270000,"text":"I mean it was very dramatic diplomacy."},{"time":273000,"text":"We went through several wars"},{"time":275000,"text":"during my time in New York."},{"time":278000,"text":"I negotiated for my country"},{"time":280000,"text":"the resolution in the Security Council"},{"time":282000,"text":"of the 12th of September 2001"},{"time":284000,"text":"condemning the attacks of the day before,"},{"time":287000,"text":"which were, of course, deeply present to us"},{"time":289000,"text":"actually living in New York at the time."},{"time":292000,"text":"So it was kind of the best of time, worst of times"},{"time":294000,"text":"kind of experience."},{"time":296000,"text":"I lived the high-life."},{"time":298000,"text":"Although I worked very long hours,"},{"time":300000,"text":"I lived in a penthouse in Union Square."},{"time":302000,"text":"I was a single British diplomat in New York City;"},{"time":305000,"text":"you can imagine what that might have meant."},{"time":307000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":310000,"text":"I had a good time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"But in 2002,"},{"time":314000,"text":"when my tour came to an end,"},{"time":317000,"text":"I decided I wasn't going to go back"},{"time":320000,"text":"to the job that was waiting for me in London."},{"time":322000,"text":"I decided to take a sabbatical,"},{"time":324000,"text":"in fact, at the New School, Bruce."},{"time":327000,"text":"In some inchoate, inarticulate way"},{"time":330000,"text":"I realized that there was something wrong"},{"time":332000,"text":"with my work, with me."},{"time":334000,"text":"I was exhausted,"},{"time":336000,"text":"and I was also disillusioned"},{"time":338000,"text":"in a way I couldn't quite put my finger on."},{"time":340000,"text":"And I decided to take some time out from work."},{"time":343000,"text":"The Foreign Office was very generous."},{"time":345000,"text":"You could take these special unpaid leave, as they called them,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and yet remain part of the diplomatic service, but not actually do any work."},{"time":350000,"text":"It was nice."},{"time":352000,"text":"And eventually, I decided"},{"time":354000,"text":"to take a secondment to join the U.N. in Kosovo,"},{"time":359000,"text":"which was then under U.N. administration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"And two things happened in Kosovo,"},{"time":364000,"text":"which kind of, again,"},{"time":366000,"text":"shows the randomness of life,"},{"time":368000,"text":"because these things turned out to be"},{"time":370000,"text":"two of the pivots of my life"},{"time":372000,"text":"and helped to deliver me to the next stage."},{"time":375000,"text":"But they were random things."},{"time":377000,"text":"One was that, in the summer of 2004,"},{"time":380000,"text":"the British government, somewhat reluctantly,"},{"time":382000,"text":"decided to have an official inquiry"},{"time":384000,"text":"into the use of intelligence on WMD"},{"time":386000,"text":"in the run up to the Iraq War,"},{"time":389000,"text":"a very limited subject."},{"time":391000,"text":"And I testified to that inquiry in secret."},{"time":394000,"text":"I had been steeped in the intelligence on Iraq"},{"time":397000,"text":"and its WMD,"},{"time":399000,"text":"and my testimony to the inquiry said three things:"},{"time":402000,"text":"that the government exaggerated the intelligence,"},{"time":405000,"text":"which was very clear in all the years I'd read it."},{"time":408000,"text":"And indeed, our own internal assessment was very clear"},{"time":411000,"text":"that Iraq's WMD"},{"time":413000,"text":"did not pose a threat to its neighbors, let alone to us."},{"time":416000,"text":"Secondly, the government had ignored all available alternatives to war,"},{"time":419000,"text":"which in some ways"},{"time":421000,"text":"was a more discreditable thing still."},{"time":424000,"text":"The third reason, I won't go into."},{"time":426000,"text":"But anyway, I gave that testimony,"},{"time":428000,"text":"and that presented me with a crisis."},{"time":430000,"text":"What was I going to do?"},{"time":432000,"text":"This testimony was deeply critical of my colleagues,"},{"time":435000,"text":"of my ministers, who had, in my view"},{"time":437000,"text":"had perpetrated a war on a falsehood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"And so I was in crisis."},{"time":442000,"text":"And this wasn't a pretty thing."},{"time":444000,"text":"I moaned about it, I hesitated,"},{"time":446000,"text":"I went on and on and on to my long-suffering wife,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and eventually I decided to resign from the British Foreign Service."},{"time":453000,"text":"I felt -- there's a scene in the Al Pacino movie \"The Insider,\" which you may know,"},{"time":457000,"text":"where he goes back to CBS"},{"time":459000,"text":"after they've let him down over the tobacco guy,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and he goes, \"You know, I just can't do this anymore. Something's broken.\""},{"time":465000,"text":"And it was like that for me. I love that movie."},{"time":467000,"text":"I felt just something's broken."},{"time":469000,"text":"I can't actually sit with my foreign minister"},{"time":471000,"text":"or my prime minister again with a smile on my face"},{"time":473000,"text":"and do what I used to do gladly for them."},{"time":476000,"text":"So took a running leap"},{"time":479000,"text":"and jumped over the edge of a cliff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"And it was a very, very uncomfortable, unpleasant feeling."},{"time":486000,"text":"And I started to fall."},{"time":488000,"text":"And today, that fall hasn't stopped;"},{"time":491000,"text":"I'm still falling."},{"time":493000,"text":"But, in a way, I've got used to the sensation of it."},{"time":496000,"text":"And in a way, I kind of like"},{"time":498000,"text":"the sensation of it a lot better"},{"time":500000,"text":"than I like actually standing on top of the cliff,"},{"time":502000,"text":"wondering what to do."},{"time":504000,"text":"A second thing happened in Kosovo,"},{"time":506000,"text":"which kind of -- I need a quick gulp of water, forgive me."},{"time":511000,"text":"A second thing happened in Kosovo,"},{"time":513000,"text":"which kind of delivered the answer,"},{"time":515000,"text":"which I couldn't really answer,"},{"time":518000,"text":"which is, \"What do I do with my life?\""},{"time":522000,"text":"I love diplomacy --"},{"time":524000,"text":"I have no career --"},{"time":526000,"text":"I expected my entire life to be a diplomat, to be serving my country."},{"time":529000,"text":"I wanted to be an ambassador,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and my mentors, my heroes,"},{"time":533000,"text":"people who got to the top of my profession,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and here I was throwing it all away."},{"time":537000,"text":"A lot of my friends were still in it."},{"time":539000,"text":"My pension was in it."},{"time":541000,"text":"And I gave it up."},{"time":543000,"text":"And what was I going to do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"And that year, in Kosovo,"},{"time":547000,"text":"this terrible, terrible thing happened, which I saw."},{"time":550000,"text":"In March 2004, there were terrible riots"},{"time":552000,"text":"all over the province -- as it then was -- of Kosovo."},{"time":555000,"text":"18 people were killed."},{"time":557000,"text":"It was anarchy."},{"time":559000,"text":"And it's a very horrible thing to see anarchy,"},{"time":561000,"text":"to know that the police and the military --"},{"time":563000,"text":"there were lots of military troops there --"},{"time":565000,"text":"actually can't stop that rampaging mob"},{"time":567000,"text":"who's coming down the street."},{"time":569000,"text":"And the only way that rampaging mob coming down the street will stop"},{"time":572000,"text":"is when they decide to stop"},{"time":574000,"text":"and when they've had enough burning and killing."},{"time":576000,"text":"And that is not a very nice feeling to see, and I saw it."},{"time":579000,"text":"And I went through it. I went through those mobs."},{"time":582000,"text":"And with my Albanian friends, we tried to stop it, but we failed."},{"time":585000,"text":"And that riot taught me something,"},{"time":588000,"text":"which isn't immediately obvious and it's kind of a complicated story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"But one of the reasons that riot took place --"},{"time":593000,"text":"those riots, which went on for several days, took place --"},{"time":595000,"text":"was because the Kosovo people"},{"time":597000,"text":"were disenfranchised from their own future."},{"time":601000,"text":"There were diplomatic negotiations about the future of Kosovo"},{"time":604000,"text":"going on then,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and the Kosovo government, let alone the Kosovo people,"},{"time":608000,"text":"were not actually"},{"time":610000,"text":"participating in those talks."},{"time":612000,"text":"There was this whole fancy diplomatic system,"},{"time":615000,"text":"this negotiation process about the future of Kosovo,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and the Kosovars weren't part of it."},{"time":620000,"text":"And funnily enough, they were frustrated about that."},{"time":623000,"text":"Those riots were part of the manifestation of that frustration."},{"time":626000,"text":"It wasn't the only reason,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and life is not simple, one reason narratives."},{"time":630000,"text":"It was a complicated thing,"},{"time":632000,"text":"and I'm not pretending it was more simple than it was."},{"time":634000,"text":"But that was one of the reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"And that kind of gave me the inspiration --"},{"time":638000,"text":"or rather to be precise,"},{"time":640000,"text":"it gave my wife the inspiration."},{"time":642000,"text":"She said, \"Why don't you advise the Kosovars?"},{"time":645000,"text":"Why don't you advise their government on their diplomacy?\""},{"time":648000,"text":"And the Kosovars were not allowed a diplomatic service."},{"time":650000,"text":"They were not allowed diplomats."},{"time":652000,"text":"They were not allowed a foreign office"},{"time":654000,"text":"to help them deal with this immensely complicated process,"},{"time":657000,"text":"which became known as the Final Status Process of Kosovo."},{"time":660000,"text":"And so that was the idea."},{"time":662000,"text":"That was the origin of the thing that became Independent Diplomat,"},{"time":664000,"text":"the world's first diplomatic advisory group"},{"time":667000,"text":"and a non-profit to boot."},{"time":669000,"text":"And it began when I flew back from London"},{"time":672000,"text":"after my time at the U.N. in Kosovo."},{"time":675000,"text":"I flew back and had dinner with the Kosovo prime minister and said to him,"},{"time":678000,"text":"\"Look, I'm proposing that I come and advise you on the diplomacy."},{"time":681000,"text":"I know this stuff. It's what I do. Why don't I come and help you?\""},{"time":684000,"text":"And he raised his glass of raki to me and said,"},{"time":686000,"text":"\"Yes, Carne. Come.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"And I came to Kosovo"},{"time":690000,"text":"and advised the Kosovo government."},{"time":692000,"text":"Independent Diplomat ended up advising three successive Kosovo prime ministers"},{"time":695000,"text":"and the multi-party negotiation team of Kosovo."},{"time":698000,"text":"And Kosovo became independent."},{"time":701000,"text":"Independent Diplomat is now established"},{"time":704000,"text":"in five diplomatic centers around the world,"},{"time":706000,"text":"and we're advising seven or eight"},{"time":708000,"text":"different countries, or political groups,"},{"time":711000,"text":"depending on how you wish to define them --"},{"time":713000,"text":"and I'm not big on definitions."},{"time":715000,"text":"We're advising the Northern Cypriots on how to reunify their island."},{"time":718000,"text":"We're advising the Burmese opposition,"},{"time":720000,"text":"the government of Southern Sudan,"},{"time":722000,"text":"which -- you heard it here first --"},{"time":724000,"text":"is going to be a new country within the next few years."},{"time":728000,"text":"We're advising the Polisario Front of the Western Sahara,"},{"time":731000,"text":"who are fighting to get their country back"},{"time":733000,"text":"from Moroccan occupation"},{"time":735000,"text":"after 34 years of dispossession."},{"time":738000,"text":"We're advising various island states in the climate change negotiations,"},{"time":741000,"text":"which is suppose to culminate"},{"time":743000,"text":"in Copenhagen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"There's a bit of randomness here too"},{"time":748000,"text":"because, when I was beginning Independent Diplomat,"},{"time":750000,"text":"I went to a party in the House of Lords,"},{"time":752000,"text":"which is a ridiculous place,"},{"time":754000,"text":"but I was holding my drink like this, and I bumped into"},{"time":756000,"text":"this guy who was standing behind me."},{"time":758000,"text":"And we started talking, and he said --"},{"time":760000,"text":"I told him what I was doing,"},{"time":762000,"text":"and I told him rather grandly"},{"time":764000,"text":"I was going to establish Independent Diplomat in New York."},{"time":766000,"text":"At that time there was just me --"},{"time":768000,"text":"and me and my wife were moving back to New York."},{"time":770000,"text":"And he said, \"Why don't you see my colleagues in New York?\""},{"time":773000,"text":"And it turned out"},{"time":775000,"text":"he worked for an innovation company called ?What If!,"},{"time":777000,"text":"which some of you have probably heard of."},{"time":779000,"text":"And one thing led to another,"},{"time":781000,"text":"and I ended up having a desk"},{"time":783000,"text":"in ?What If! in New York,"},{"time":785000,"text":"when I started Independent Diplomat."},{"time":787000,"text":"And watching ?What If!"},{"time":789000,"text":"develop new flavors of chewing gum for Wrigley"},{"time":791000,"text":"or new flavors for Coke"},{"time":793000,"text":"actually helped me innovate"},{"time":795000,"text":"new strategies for the Kosovars"},{"time":797000,"text":"and for the Saharawis of the Western Sahara."},{"time":800000,"text":"And I began to realize that there are different ways of doing diplomacy --"},{"time":803000,"text":"that diplomacy, like business,"},{"time":805000,"text":"is a business of solving problems,"},{"time":807000,"text":"and yet the word innovation doesn't exist in diplomacy;"},{"time":810000,"text":"it's all zero sum games and realpolitik"},{"time":813000,"text":"and ancient institutions that have been there for generations"},{"time":816000,"text":"and do things the same way they've always done things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"And Independent Diplomat, today,"},{"time":821000,"text":"tries to incorporate some of the things I learned at ?What If!."},{"time":824000,"text":"We all sit in one office and shout at each other across the office."},{"time":827000,"text":"We all work on little laptops and try to move desks to change the way we think."},{"time":830000,"text":"And we use naive experts"},{"time":832000,"text":"who may know nothing about the countries we're dealing with,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but may know something about something else"},{"time":837000,"text":"to try to inject new thinking"},{"time":839000,"text":"into the problems"},{"time":841000,"text":"that we try to address for our clients."},{"time":843000,"text":"It's not easy, because our clients, by definition,"},{"time":845000,"text":"are having a difficult time, diplomatically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850000,"text":"There are, I don't know,"},{"time":852000,"text":"some lessons from all of this,"},{"time":855000,"text":"personal and political --"},{"time":857000,"text":"and in a way, they're the same thing."},{"time":860000,"text":"The personal one"},{"time":862000,"text":"is falling off a cliff"},{"time":864000,"text":"is actually a good thing, and I recommend it."},{"time":868000,"text":"And it's a good thing to do at least once in your life"},{"time":870000,"text":"just to tear everything up and jump."},{"time":874000,"text":"The second thing is a bigger lesson about the world today."},{"time":877000,"text":"Independent Diplomat is part of a trend"},{"time":880000,"text":"which is emerging and evident across the world,"},{"time":883000,"text":"which is that the world is fragmenting."},{"time":886000,"text":"States mean less than they used to,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and the power of the state is declining."},{"time":891000,"text":"That means the power of others things is rising."},{"time":893000,"text":"Those other things are called non-state actors."},{"time":895000,"text":"They may be corporations,"},{"time":897000,"text":"they may be mafiosi, they may be nice NGOs,"},{"time":900000,"text":"they may anything,"},{"time":902000,"text":"any number of things."},{"time":904000,"text":"We are living in a more complicated and fragmented world."},{"time":907000,"text":"If governments are less able"},{"time":909000,"text":"to affect the problems"},{"time":911000,"text":"that affect us in the world,"},{"time":914000,"text":"then that means, who is left to deal with them,"},{"time":917000,"text":"who has to take greater responsibility to deal with them?"},{"time":919000,"text":"Us."},{"time":921000,"text":"If they can't do it, who's left to deal with it?"},{"time":924000,"text":"We have no choice but to embrace that reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":927000,"text":"What this means is"},{"time":929000,"text":"it's no longer good enough"},{"time":932000,"text":"to say that international relations, or global affairs,"},{"time":935000,"text":"or chaos in Somalia,"},{"time":937000,"text":"or what's going on in Burma is none of your business,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and that you can leave it to governments to get on with."},{"time":943000,"text":"I can connect any one of you"},{"time":945000,"text":"by six degrees of separation"},{"time":947000,"text":"to the Al-Shabaab militia in Somalia."},{"time":950000,"text":"Ask me how later, particularly if you eat fish, interestingly enough,"},{"time":954000,"text":"but that connection is there."},{"time":956000,"text":"We are all intimately connected."},{"time":958000,"text":"And this isn't just Tom Friedman,"},{"time":960000,"text":"it's actually provable in case after case after case."},{"time":963000,"text":"What that means is, instead of asking your politicians to do things,"},{"time":966000,"text":"you have to look to yourself to do things."},{"time":969000,"text":"And Independent Diplomat is a kind of example of this"},{"time":971000,"text":"in a sort of loose way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":973000,"text":"There aren't neat examples, but one example is this:"},{"time":976000,"text":"the way the world is changing"},{"time":978000,"text":"is embodied in what's going on at the place I used to work --"},{"time":980000,"text":"the U.N. Security Council."},{"time":982000,"text":"The U.N. was established in 1945."},{"time":985000,"text":"Its charter is basically designed"},{"time":987000,"text":"to stop conflicts between states --"},{"time":989000,"text":"interstate conflict."},{"time":991000,"text":"Today, 80 percent of the agenda"},{"time":993000,"text":"of the U.N. Security Council"},{"time":995000,"text":"is about conflicts within states,"},{"time":997000,"text":"involving non-state parties --"},{"time":999000,"text":"guerillas, separatists,"},{"time":1001000,"text":"terrorists, if you want to call them that,"},{"time":1003000,"text":"people who are not normal governments, who are not normal states."},{"time":1006000,"text":"That is the state of the world today."},{"time":1009000,"text":"When I realized this,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"and when I look back on my time at the Security Council"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and what happened with the Kosovars,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and I realize that often"},{"time":1018000,"text":"the people who were most directly affected"},{"time":1020000,"text":"by what we were doing in the Security Council"},{"time":1022000,"text":"weren't actually there, weren't actually invited"},{"time":1024000,"text":"to give their views to the Security Council,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"I thought, this is wrong."},{"time":1028000,"text":"Something's got to be done about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030000,"text":"So I started off in a traditional mode."},{"time":1033000,"text":"Me and my colleagues at Independent Diplomat"},{"time":1035000,"text":"went around the U.N. Security Council."},{"time":1037000,"text":"We went around 70 U.N. member states --"},{"time":1039000,"text":"the Kazaks, the Ethiopians, the Israelis --"},{"time":1041000,"text":"you name them, we went to see them --"},{"time":1043000,"text":"the secretary general, all of them,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"and said, \"This is all wrong."},{"time":1047000,"text":"This is terrible that you don't consult these people who are actually affected."},{"time":1049000,"text":"You've got to institutionalize a system"},{"time":1051000,"text":"where you actually invite the Kosovars"},{"time":1053000,"text":"to come and tell you what they think."},{"time":1055000,"text":"This will allow you to tell me -- you can tell them what you think."},{"time":1057000,"text":"It'll be great. You can have an exchange."},{"time":1059000,"text":"You can actually incorporate these people's views into your decisions,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"which means your decisions will be more effective and durable.\""},{"time":1067000,"text":"Super-logical, you would think."},{"time":1069000,"text":"I mean, incredibly logical. So obvious, anybody could get it."},{"time":1071000,"text":"And of course, everybody got it. Everybody went, \"Yes, of course, you're absolutely right."},{"time":1074000,"text":"Come back to us"},{"time":1076000,"text":"in maybe six months.\""},{"time":1078000,"text":"And of course, nothing happened -- nobody did anything."},{"time":1081000,"text":"The Security Council does its business"},{"time":1083000,"text":"in exactly the same way today"},{"time":1085000,"text":"that it did X number of years ago,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"when I was there 10 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091000,"text":"So we looked at that observation"},{"time":1093000,"text":"of basically failure"},{"time":1095000,"text":"and thought, what can we do about it."},{"time":1097000,"text":"And I thought, I'm buggered"},{"time":1099000,"text":"if I'm going to spend the rest of my life"},{"time":1101000,"text":"lobbying for these crummy governments"},{"time":1103000,"text":"to do what needs to be done."},{"time":1105000,"text":"So what we're going to do"},{"time":1107000,"text":"is we're actually going to set up these meetings ourselves."},{"time":1109000,"text":"So now, Independent Diplomat"},{"time":1111000,"text":"is in the process of setting up meetings"},{"time":1113000,"text":"between the U.N. Security Council"},{"time":1115000,"text":"and the parties to the disputes"},{"time":1117000,"text":"that are on the agenda of the Security Council."},{"time":1120000,"text":"So we will be bringing"},{"time":1122000,"text":"Darfuri rebel groups,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"the Northern Cypriots and the Southern Cypriots,"},{"time":1129000,"text":"rebels from Aceh,"},{"time":1132000,"text":"and awful long laundry list"},{"time":1134000,"text":"of chaotic conflicts around the world."},{"time":1137000,"text":"And we will be trying to bring the parties to New York"},{"time":1140000,"text":"to sit down in a quiet room"},{"time":1142000,"text":"in a private setting with no press"},{"time":1144000,"text":"and actually explain what they want"},{"time":1146000,"text":"to the members of the U. N. Security Council,"},{"time":1148000,"text":"and for the members of the U.N. Security Council"},{"time":1150000,"text":"to explain to them what they want."},{"time":1152000,"text":"So there's actually a conversation,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"which has never before happened."},{"time":1156000,"text":"And of course, describing all this,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"any of you who know politics will think this is incredibly difficult,"},{"time":1162000,"text":"and I entirely agree with you."},{"time":1164000,"text":"The chances of failure are very high,"},{"time":1167000,"text":"but it certainly won't happen"},{"time":1169000,"text":"if we don't try to make it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172000,"text":"And my politics has changed fundamentally"},{"time":1175000,"text":"from when I was a diplomat to what I am today,"},{"time":1177000,"text":"and I think that outputs is what matters, not process,"},{"time":1180000,"text":"not technology, frankly, so much either."},{"time":1183000,"text":"Preach technology"},{"time":1185000,"text":"to all the Twittering members of all the Iranian demonstrations"},{"time":1188000,"text":"who are now in political prison in Tehran,"},{"time":1191000,"text":"where Ahmadinejad remains in power."},{"time":1193000,"text":"Technology has not delivered political change in Iran."},{"time":1197000,"text":"You've got to look at the outputs, and you got to say to yourself,"},{"time":1200000,"text":"\"What can I do to produce that particular output?\""},{"time":1202000,"text":"That is the politics of the 21st century,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"and in a way, Independent Diplomat"},{"time":1207000,"text":"embodies that fragmentation, that change,"},{"time":1210000,"text":"that is happening to all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1214000,"text":"That's my story. Thanks."}]}]}